        texthead1: "How does blockchain work?",
        text: "How does blockchain work?",
        textsub1: "About Blockchain",
        text1: "Blockchain services Blockchain is a safe and transparent system for recording information that provides a new and unique way to make international payments, build computer games, improve healthcare systems, and track the supply chain of goods and services. Blockchain is an innovative technology used to store and transfer data; This technology was first introduced in 2008 by a person or group with the pseudonym Satoshi Nakamoto as the main author of the Bitcoin Whitepaper. This technology is actually a set of blocks connected to each other, in each block there are a number of transactions in the form of a list.",
        textsub2: " Starting the transaction",
        text2: "Each transaction or transaction made in the network leads to the addition of a new block in the blockchain. For example, considering Ethereum smart contract development, if you want to deposit some Ethereum to your friend's wallet, this transaction is done by creating a new block in the Ethereum ecosystem.",
        texthead2: "Approval of restrictions",
        textsub3: "",
        text3: "After registering your transfer request, the network miners will be responsible for confirming your transaction. First, new information must be entered into the system. This is done by computer. This network often consists of thousands of computers spread around the world  Your transaction must be stored in a block. After confirming the authenticity of the transaction, the amount requested for deposit and your digital signature is stored in a block. Adding blocks to the blockchain using hashing After confirming all the transactions of a block, a unique identification code called Hash must be assigned to the block. After hashing, the block can be added to the blockchain. After creating a new block in the network, this block will be available to everyone. For example, if you look at the Bitcoin blockchain, you will see that you have access to transaction data and you can see the following information: . The height of the block (Height), which is calculated based on the total number of blocks and shows that this is the largest block that is placed on the blockchain chain. . A hash block is a 64-digit code string that includes numbers and letters and starts with zero. . How long did it take to mine the block? . By whom it is mined (Miner). . What is the block size?  Blockchain security Blockchain technology offers many solutions to security and reliability problems. First, we should mention that new blocks are stored linearly based on when they are added to the storage network. For this reason, new blocks are always added to the end of the network. If you look at the Bitcoin blockchain, you will notice where each block is located on the network, which is called its height.",
        textsub4: "Blockchain security Blockchain technology",
        text4: "Blockchain security Blockchain technology offers many solutions to security and reliability problems. First, we should mention that new blocks are stored linearly based on when they are added to the storage network. For this reason, new blocks are always added to the end of the network. If you look at the Bitcoin blockchain, you will notice where each block is located on the network, which is called its height.Once the block is added to the end of the block chain, it will be very difficult to change the contents of that block. The reason for the difficulty of this change is to assign a special hash code for each block. This hash is placed next to the hash of its previous block in each block. Hash codes are created by mathematical equations that convert digital information into a string of numbers and letters. If the information of each block changes in any way, the hash code will also change. This hash code change is an important point in the security of the blockchain network. Let's say a hacker tries to edit the financial transaction information between you and Amazon and change it to make it look like you paid twice. Immediately after editing the dollar volume of the transaction, the hash code of the block is changed. But the hash code of the next block remains the same as its previous number, and the hacker must edit the information of the next block to lose his way.",
